    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="942"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d942">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50/2540</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Campbell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Chargé d’Affaires presents his compliments to the Secretary of
                    State and, with reference to the Embassy <hi rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi> of
                    August 31st, has the honour to inform Mr. Hull that the United Kingdom
                    Delegation will be led by the Right Honourable Richard K. Law, M.P.,
                    Parliamentary Under Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>2. Sir Ronald Campbell has also the honour to transmit to Mr. Hull herewith for
                    his information the substance of a telegram which has been sent by Mr. Eden to
                    His Majesty’s Ambassadors at Moscow and Chungking<note n="24" xml:id="d942fn24"
                        >Not printed.</note> with regard to the exploratory talks between
                    representatives of the United States and the United Kingdom Governments
                    envisaged by Article VII of the Mutual Aid Agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-08">September 8,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[United States and United Kingdom economic experts held informal discussions
                        at Washington with reference to article VII of the Mutual-Aid Agreement,
                        ending on October 18, 1943, at which the following general topics were
                        explored: (1) Commercial policy, (2) international commodity arrangements,
                        (3) cartels, and (4) coordination of measures to promote employment. For a
                        summary of these discussions, see <ref target="#pg_766">page 766</ref>.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
